1. What is a Flask Project Structure?

A Flask Project Structure is the organized arrangement of folders and files used to build a Flask application.

Instead of putting everything into one Python file, we separate the project into different folders.

This makes the application:

Easy to understand
Easy to maintain
Easy to upgrade
Professional
2. Why Do We Need a Project Structure?

Imagine building a restaurant.

Would you keep everything in one room?

Kitchen
Dining
Billing
Storage
Office

No.

Each department has its own place.

Similarly,

A Flask project also has separate folders.

